100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On January 29, 1926, Britains Prime Minister Stanley Baldwin addressed Parliament, emphasizing the need for national unity amidst economic challenges. In the United States, the Senate continued discussions on the pending immigration bill, stirring public debate over quotas. Meanwhile, in France, tensions rose as labor strikes disrupted industry, highlighting ongoing unrest in the post-war economy.
